1 certification attesting that the applicant meets the requirements of
2 paragraph (a) or (b) of subsection 2.
3 2. An applicant for a grant of federal money for the
4 development of broadband services and infrastructure shall
5 submit to a state agency with the application for the grant a signed
6 statement certifying that:
7 (a) If the applicant:
8 (1) Will perform some or all of the work that is financed in
9 whole or in part with the grant money or if such work will be
10 performed by a provider of broadband services, the applicant or
11 provider, as applicable, meets the requirements set forth in
12 paragraph (b) or (c); and
13 (2) Will subcontract some or all of the work that is financed
14 in whole or in part with the grant money, the subcontractor meets
15 the requirements set forth in paragraph (b) or (c);
16 (b) The applicant, provider of broadband services or
17 contractor, as applicable:
18 (1) Has a training program that is appropriate for the work
19 to be performed by the applicant, provider or contractor, as
20 applicable, and is capable of providing, upon request,
21 documentation that:
22 (I) Demonstrates that the applicant, provider or
23 contractor, as applicable, has the ability and financial means to
24 provide such a training program;
25 (II) Shows that the applicant, provider or contractor, as
26 applicable, has a recruitment policy and an equal opportunity
27 policy;
28 (III) Shows that the applicant, provider or contractor, as
29 applicable, provides, at least twice each year, information
30 concerning the content of the training program and the times at
31 which the training program is offered; and
32 (IV) Demonstrates that the applicant, provider or
33 contractor, as applicable, has actually provided the training
34 program before submitting the application;
35 (2) Requires safety training, including, without limitation,
36 an OSHA-10 course for employees and an OSHA-30 course for
37 supervisory employees, that is appropriate for the work to be
38 performed;
39 (3) Requires work performed by the applicant, provider or
40 contractor, as applicable, that is financed in whole or in part with
41 the grant money will be performed by employees who are directly
42 employed by the applicant, provider or contractor, as applicable,
43 and that such workers will receive high-quality wages that are not
44 less than the appropriate prevailing wage in the region determined
