13 3. Any certification submitted by an applicant for a grant
14 pursuant to subsection 2 must be made available on the Internet
15 website of the state agency which awarded the grant.
16 4. In addition to the requirements of subsections 1 and 2 and
17 except as otherwise provided in federal law, each state agency
18 shall require as a condition of any grant of federal money for the
19 development of broadband services and infrastructure in
20 accordance with federal law that is awarded by the state agency
21 that:
22 (a) Any certification provided by the applicant pursuant to
23 subsection 2 is binding upon the applicant who is awarded the
24 grant money; and
25 (b) If an applicant, provider of broadband services or
26 contractor performs any work that requires a contractor’s license
27 issued pursuant to chapter 624 of NRS and is financed in whole or
28 in part with the grant money, the provisions of NRS 338.020 to
29 338.090, inclusive, shall apply.
30 5. If any federal statute or regulation precludes the granting
31 of federal assistance or reduces the amount of that assistance for a
32 particular grant because of the provisions of this section, the
33 provisions of this section do not apply insofar as their application
34 would preclude or reduce federal assistance for that work.
35 6. Any state agency that awards a grant of federal money for
36 the development of broadband services and infrastructure
37 pursuant to this section may adopt regulations to carry out the
38 provisions of this section.
